text: Winschoten is a small city in the province of Groningen, the Netherlands. Since 2010, it has been a part of the municipality of Oldambt. It has about 18,000 people (2013). There is a railway station with direct connections to Groningen and Leer (Germany). ==References== ==Other websites== * * Category:21st-century disestablishments in the Netherlands Category:Cities in Groningen (province) Category:Former municipalities of Groningen (province) Category:Oldambt
